abstract = {We focus on nDCG choice of gains, and in particular on the fracture between large differences in exponential gains of high relevance labels and the not-so-small confusion, or inconsistency, between these labels in data. We show that better gains can be derived from data by measuring the label inconsistency, to the point that virtually indistinguishable labels correspond to equal gains. Our derived optimal gains make a better nDCG objective for training Learning to Rank algorithms.},
